**What it covers:**
- **Three-layer navigation architecture**: primary (sidebar/bottom nav), secondary (header), tertiary (in-page tabs)
- **Desktop sidebar**: 8 prioritized items in 4 sections (Main, AI Tutor, Learning, Account) with expandable Practice & Progress groups
- **Mobile bottom nav**: 5 items (Home, Plan, AI, Vocab, Progress) with overflow pattern for secondary pages
- **Header bar**: page title, search, AI Tutor shortcut, dark mode toggle, user menu — responsive across breakpoints
- **AI Tutor entry points**: 9 distinct surfaces (sidebar, bottom nav, floating button, header, contextual CTAs) all leading to one consistent experience
- **User profile menu**: avatar dropdown with profile, settings, progress, language toggle, sign out
- **Active states**: text + background + left border accent (not color-only), breadcrumbs for sub-pages
- **Responsive behavior**: 3 breakpoints (≥1024px / 768-1023px / <768px), safe areas, touch targets ≥48px
- **Accessibility**: ARIA landmarks, `aria-current="page"`, skip link, reduced motion, keyboard navigation
- **Current vs. proposed comparison**: table mapping 17 flat items → 8 prioritized items with hubs
